  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: Floating \"+\" button covers the delete button:\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/42265385-aebf549c-7f73-11e8-94ff-8581e279f20a.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Have long list of chats\r\n- Swipe a chat on the bottom to delete it \r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: nightly, 4 July\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n### UX insight\r\nIn ux research (RRR8) we found that longpress wroked for reply/copy message with all participants. In the few cases it needed multiple attempts it showed to be easily discoverable. \r\nhttps://docs.google.com/presentation/d/10qb5jRXwRT9lYkxrn8Ui5Bov_JRuf1WBaPqSXd0ZAtY/edit#slide=id.g3f411e60e9_0_155",
