    "body": "What we could do is create an exception that if you swipe a cell that is partially covered by a FAB, the FAB would move its position 1:1 along with the cell (animate it on a X axis). But a better alternative would be to change the swipe mechanism so that instead of tapping the uncovered button to delete, you'd only have to swipe for a set minimum distance: after you'd swiped for say 60 points we'd register the delete action. It's popular among apps I use and allows for faster triage of unwanted chats/dapps, if hard to explain I can create a prototype for this behaviour. What you think @andmironov ?",
