    "body": "@errorists I like the long-press interaction more than swipe to delete. Here is my reasoning:\r\n\r\n1. In the near future, we may want to consider swiping between Home, Wallet and Profile tabs on Android. If so, swipe to delete may interfere with swiping between tabs\r\n2. Long-press can display menu with additional options like \"Mark as read\" or \"Pin to the top\". It's a good place to display them. Telegram does it and it does not have swipe gesture.\r\n3. We've seen some bug reports about our swipe to delete gesture. E.g. that it brakes UI when swiped to the left and then back to the right\r\n4. If we go with swipe to delete, I'd ask for additional confirmation (show a modal). Alternatively, show a status bar with a revert button\r\n\r\ncc @andmironov ",
