    "body": "@lukaszfryc All good points! \r\n\r\n1. I've considered this heavily, but in the context of having separate tabs inside the Home screen, for example swiping between Chats, Group Chats and Dapps.\r\n2. Technically we could allow for additional actions inside the swipe gesture, exposing different buttons by swiping from left and right. Depending on how often you access those actions, gestures might be more convenient, but that's not saying either is worse, just more appropriate for different actions.\r\n3. Agree there, our current implementation is lacking. It doesn't follow the finger properly, it's jerky in movement and buggy, when dragged past its bounds a white rectangle would slowly cover the text. That would be my main reason to go with a menu, unless we can make the swipe gesture nicely designed and implemented we shouldn't be introducing them at all.\r\n4. Agree, I've already updated it with an alert prompt after feedback but a snackbar with Undo button would be even nicer.\r\n",
