    "body": "> 1. I've considered this heavily, but in the context of having separate tabs inside the Home screen, for example swiping between Chats, Group Chats and Dapps.\r\n\r\nGood idea. It's how Facebook Messenger works. And, because of that, the app uses long press instead of swipe to delete a chat. \r\n\r\n> 2. Technically we could allow for additional actions inside the swipe gesture, exposing different buttons by swiping from left and right. Depending on how often you access those actions, gestures might be more convenient, but that's not saying either is worse, just more appropriate for different actions.\r\n\r\nSwipe gesture maybe a bit more convenient if you have lot of items to remove. But only a little since you need to confirm each action anyway (delete dialog). If you want to remove many chats or dapps quickly, I'd consider some bulk action (option to select many items). But, it's not needed now.\r\n \r\n> 4. Agree, I've already updated it with an alert prompt after feedback but a snackbar with Undo button would be even nicer.\r\n\r\nI'd keep it simple now and use dialog. We already show it when you want to remove a chat while being on the chat screen. You click chat menu, press delete and confirm in the dialog.\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n@errorists summing up, do you think we should remove swipe to delete and go with long press? Can we have opinion of other designers, @andmironov?",
