    "body": "Shame on me but I have just discovered that you can remove chats with the long press on FB messenger. Can it be considerated as a not popular behavior?  I like the idea of adding some new options to the context menu though. \r\n\r\nI personally would try to focus on current problems and needs. Yeah, maybe in the near future we will need a swipe between home tab categories, but most likely we will create a separate tab for dapps and browser. Nobody sure yet.  \r\n\r\nTo summarize: I would use this to solve our particular problem here.  \r\n\r\n> Only have to swipe for a set minimum distance: after you'd swiped for say 60 points we'd register the delete action. It's popular among apps I use and allows for faster triage of unwanted chats/dapps",
